document_data.Combat:
Being only semi-intelligent, spellhaunts could not employ complex tactics. However, they could sense magic up to {{SI|300|ft|long=yes}} away for each effective spell a victim had on them. This made it simple for spellhaunts to locate potential opponents. 

The attacks of spellhaunts ignored all armor, and inflicted moderate damage, as well as stripping magical [[enchantment]]s. They were immune to all spells, except for those that cancelled magic, such as ''[[dispel magic]]''.
{{fq
|text=Want to see a [[wizard]] jump out of his skin? Just wait till he's looking another way and yell, "Spellhaunt! Spellhaunt!" Gets 'em every time, friend.
|source=Irvidigannizid, [[gnome]] prankster
}}
